\sum_{n=4}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n^{2}-1}
1/(n-1)-1/(n+1) = 2/(n^2-1) 
\sum_{n=4}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^2-1} = (1/2)\sum_{n=4}^{\infty} \left(\frac{1}{n-1} - \frac{1}{n+1}\right) = \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{4} 
\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{4}\right)
\sum_{n=a}^b \frac{1}{n^2-1}
